                    <physDesc>
                        <objectDesc>
                            <supportDesc>
                                <support><p>A grey marble plaque, intact on the upper and right sides, seemingly damaged on the left and lower sides, although the text appears complete, and the stone tapers to the lower edge (the layout may imply that a balancing hedera is missing upper left, but the clear lack of such on line 3 is probably against this). The rear is rough and uneven, with traces of mortar.</p>
                                    <material ana="#material.stone.marble" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html">marble</material>
                                    <objectType ana="#object.plaque" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259">plaque</objectType>
                                    <dimensions>
                                        <height unit="cm">20.8</height>
                                        <width unit="cm">25.4</width>
                                        <depth unit="cm">2.9 (maximum)</depth>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </support>
                                <condition ana="#condition.damaged"/>
		    </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout><p>Five lines, approximately centred on the stone, except for line 5 which is aligned to the left margin.</p>
                                    <rs ana="#execution.chiselled" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1">chiselled</rs>
                                	<damage ana="#text_condition.complete"/>
			</layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote><p>Letters plain and somewhat crudely v-cut, without serifs, of regular height. Alpha with broken and straight bar; regular quadrate epsilon and sigma; theta close to rhomboid; mu with diagonal strokes, middle strokes meet at half height; nu with diagonal joining well above the baseline; phi is rhomboid and extended; uncial omega.</p>
                                <locus from="line1" to="line4">Line 1-4</locus>
                                <dimensions type="letterHeight">
                                    <height unit="mm">23-26 (omega 22, phi 36)</height>
                                </dimensions>
                                <locus from="line5" to="line5">Line 5</locus>
                                <dimensions type="letterHeight">
                                    <height unit="mm">18-20</height>
                                </dimensions>
                                <locus from="line1" to="line2">Interlineation line 1 to 2</locus>
                                <dimensions type="interlinear">
                                    <height unit="mm"/>
                                </dimensions>
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>
                    </physDesc>
